## Quick reference

| Need to… | Do it in… | How |
|----------|------------|-----|
| Fetch when a route is opened | redux.ts | Middleware on `router/navigateSuccess` → dispatch thunk |
| Debounce or poll | redux.ts | Middleware (timers, clear on route leave) |
| Navigate | react.tsx or thunk | `dispatch(navigateTo({ name, params?, search? }) as never)` |
| Read state | react.tsx | `useAppSelector(selector)` |
| Trigger an action (e.g. refresh) | react.tsx | `dispatch(myThunk())` |
| API call | redux.ts | `createAsyncThunk` |
| Derived data | redux.ts | Selectors (don’t store derived data in state) |

| Debug headlessly | Node script | Same Pi config + `createDebugMiddleware()` or `createTraceMiddleware(path)` from `pi` |

For more detail and patterns (e.g. polling, debounce), see `packages/pi/README.md`.

